## 4. Database Schema

```mermaid
erDiagram
    USERS {
        uuid id PK
        string email UK
        string password_hash
        enum role "ADMIN | DRIVER | USER"
        string first_name
        string last_name
        string phone
        string zip_code
        string city
        timestamp created_at
        timestamp updated_at
    }

    DRIVER_PROFILES {
        uuid id PK
        uuid user_id FK
        string license_number
        string vehicle_make
        string vehicle_model
        int vehicle_year
        string vehicle_color
        string license_plate
        float avg_rating
        int total_rides
        boolean is_available
        string service_zip_codes "comma-separated"
    }

    RIDES {
        uuid id PK
        uuid user_id FK
        uuid driver_id FK "nullable until accepted"
        string from_address
        string from_zip
        float from_lat
        float from_lng
        string to_address
        string to_zip
        float to_lat
        float to_lng
        decimal price "set by user"
        enum status "PENDING | ACCEPTED | IN_PROGRESS | COMPLETED | CANCELLED"
        timestamp created_at
        timestamp accepted_at
        timestamp completed_at
    }

    RIDE_REQUESTS {
        uuid id PK
        uuid ride_id FK
        uuid driver_id FK
        enum status "PENDING | ACCEPTED | REJECTED"
        timestamp created_at
    }

    RATINGS {
        uuid id PK
        uuid ride_id FK
        uuid rated_by FK
        uuid rated_user FK
        int score "1-5"
        string comment
        timestamp created_at
    }

    USERS ||--o| DRIVER_PROFILES : "has (if driver)"
    USERS ||--o{ RIDES : "requests"
    DRIVER_PROFILES ||--o{ RIDES : "drives"
    RIDES ||--o{ RIDE_REQUESTS : "has"
    RIDES ||--o{ RATINGS : "has"
    USERS ||--o{ RATINGS : "gives/receives"
```

---

## 5. Core API Endpoints

### Auth
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/auth/register` | Register (role: user/driver) |
| POST | `/api/auth/login` | Login → JWT |
| GET | `/api/auth/me` | Current user profile |

### Rides (User)
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/rides` | Create ride (from, to, price) |
| GET | `/api/rides/my` | User's ride history |
| GET | `/api/rides/:id/drivers` | Available drivers for a ride |
| PUT | `/api/rides/:id/pick-driver` | User picks a driver |
| PUT | `/api/rides/:id/cancel` | Cancel ride |

### Rides (Driver)
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | `/api/driver/requests` | Pending ride requests |
| PUT | `/api/driver/requests/:id/accept` | Accept a ride |
| PUT | `/api/driver/requests/:id/reject` | Reject a ride |
| PUT | `/api/rides/:id/complete` | Mark ride complete |

### Admin
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | `/api/admin/rides` | All rides (filterable) |
| GET | `/api/admin/users` | All users |
| GET | `/api/admin/drivers` | All drivers + stats |
| GET | `/api/admin/stats` | Dashboard stats |

### Users
| Method | Endpoint | Description |
|--------|----------|-------------|
| GET | `/api/users/:id` | User profile |
| PUT | `/api/users/:id` | Update profile |
| POST | `/api/ratings` | Submit a rating |

---

## 6. Ride Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant API as Backend API
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant D as Driver

    U->>API: POST /rides (from, to, price)
    API->>DB: Create ride (status: PENDING)
    API->>DB: Find drivers by matching zip_code
    API-->>U: Ride created + list of matching drivers

    U->>API: PUT /rides/:id/pick-driver (driver_id)
    API->>DB: Create RIDE_REQUEST for selected driver
    API-->>D: 🔔 Notification (Socket.IO)

    D->>API: PUT /driver/requests/:id/accept
    API->>DB: Update ride (status: ACCEPTED, assign driver)
    API-->>U: 🔔 Driver accepted! (exchange contact info)

    D->>API: PUT /rides/:id/complete
    API->>DB: Update ride (status: COMPLETED)
    API-->>U: 🔔 Ride completed
    U->>API: POST /ratings (score, comment)
```

---

## 7. Developer Assignment Plan (4 Developers)

### Developer Roles

| Dev | Focus Area | Responsibilities |
|-----|-----------|-----------------|
| **Dev 1** | Backend Core | Auth, database schema, Prisma, API scaffolding, middleware |
| **Dev 2** | Backend Features | Ride CRUD, driver matching, ratings, Socket.IO |
| **Dev 3** | Frontend — User & Driver | User portal, driver portal, map integration |
| **Dev 4** | Frontend — Admin & Shared | Admin dashboard, shared components, deployment |

---

### Sprint Plan (8 Weeks)

#### Sprint 1 — Foundation (Weeks 1–2)

| Dev | Tasks |
|-----|-------|
| **Dev 1** | Set up monorepo, Prisma schema, DB migrations, auth endpoints (register/login/JWT), middleware |
| **Dev 2** | Set up Express project structure, basic ride CRUD endpoints, input validation |
| **Dev 3** | Set up Next.js, design system tokens, auth pages (login/register), layout & navigation |
| **Dev 4** | Shared component library (buttons, forms, cards, modals), Docker Compose for local dev |

> **Milestone**: Users can register, log in, and see a dashboard shell.

#### Sprint 2 — Core Features (Weeks 3–4)

| Dev | Tasks |
|-----|-------|
| **Dev 1** | User & driver profile APIs, driver profile CRUD, role-based access control |
| **Dev 2** | Driver matching by zip code, ride request flow, ride status transitions |
| **Dev 3** | Ride creation form with map (Leaflet), address autocomplete, ride history page |
| **Dev 4** | Admin dashboard — user list, driver list with stats, ride overview table |

> **Milestone**: Full ride creation → driver matching → acceptance flow works end-to-end.

#### Sprint 3 — User Picks Driver & Realtime (Weeks 5–6)

| Dev | Tasks |
|-----|-------|
| **Dev 1** | Ratings API, driving history aggregation, Socket.IO backend setup |
| **Dev 2** | User picks driver feature (browse drivers, see ratings), ride notifications |
| **Dev 3** | Driver portal — incoming requests, accept/reject UI, active ride view, contact exchange |
| **Dev 4** | Admin stats dashboard (charts), ride status filters, driver approval workflow |

> **Milestone**: User can browse drivers, pick one, driver gets notified and accepts. Admin sees everything.

#### Sprint 4 — Polish & Deploy (Weeks 7–8)

| Dev | Tasks |
|-----|-------|
| **Dev 1** | API hardening, error handling, rate limiting, seed scripts for demo data |
| **Dev 2** | End-to-end testing, API integration tests, bug fixes |
| **Dev 3** | Responsive design polish, loading states, error boundaries, UX improvements |
| **Dev 4** | CI/CD pipeline (GitHub Actions), deployment to Render/Railway, documentation |

> **Milestone**: Deployed, working POC ready for 100 users.

