## 8. Infrastructure & Hosting (Low-Cost Strategy)

> [!TIP]
> For a **100-user POC**, you can run everything on free tiers. Upgrade only when you outgrow them.

| Service | Provider | Cost | Notes |
|---------|----------|------|-------|
| **Frontend hosting** | [Vercel](https://vercel.com) | **Free** | Perfect for Next.js, 100 GB bandwidth |
| **Backend API** | [Render](https://render.com) | **Free** | Free web service (spins down when idle) |
| **PostgreSQL** | [Neon](https://neon.tech) | **Free** | 0.5 GB storage, serverless Postgres |
| **Domain** | Optional | ~$12/yr | Use `.com` or free subdomain from Render/Vercel |
| **CI/CD** | GitHub Actions | **Free** | Unlimited for public repos |
| **Monitoring** | [Better Stack](https://betterstack.com) | **Free** | Basic uptime monitoring |
| **Email (optional)** | [Resend](https://resend.com) | **Free** | 100 emails/day on free tier |

### Estimated Monthly Cost

| Scenario | Cost |
|----------|------|
| **POC (100 users)** | **$0 – $12** (domain only) |
| **Growing (500 users)** | ~$20/mo (paid Render + larger DB) |
| **Scale (1000+ users)** | ~$50–100/mo (dedicated instances) |

---

## 9. Development Environment Setup

```bash
# Prerequisites
node >= 20, npm >= 10, Docker Desktop

# Clone & install
git clone https://github.com/<org>/DollarToGo.git
cd DollarToGo
npm install          # installs all workspace deps

# Start local database
docker compose up -d  # Postgres on :5432

# Run migrations
cd apps/api && npx prisma migrate dev

# Start dev servers
npm run dev          # starts both frontend (:3000) and backend (:4000)
```

---

## 10. Future Enhancements (Post-POC)

- **Payment integration** (Stripe) — hold/release model
- **Real-time GPS tracking** — driver location on map
- **Push notifications** — mobile PWA support
- **Advanced matching algorithm** — rating, distance, price factors
- **Driver document verification** — license, insurance upload
- **Ride scheduling** — book rides in advance
- **Chat** — in-app messaging between user and driver

